-- UBS Taps Bank of America's Uran as Global Co-Head of Emerging Fixed Income
-- Ambereen Choudhury
-- 2010-06-16T14:12:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/ubs-hires-uran-from-bank-of-america-for-emerging-markets-fixed-income-unit.html

          
          
             UBS AG , Switzerlandâ€™s biggest
lender, hired  Can Uran  as global co-head of fixed income,
currency and commodities for its emerging markets unit.  
 Uran, who previously ran emerging markets credit trading at
Bank of America Merrill Lynch will be based in London and start
in September, Zurich-based UBS said in a memo to staff. The
contents of the memo were confirmed by a UBS spokeswoman in
London today.  
 UBS hired  Jerome Peltier , formerly of Deutsche Bank AG, as
co-head of its investment banking unit in France on June 14.  
